Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @shallot{1}; mince half the shallot and thinly slice remaining. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise. Cut @Roma tomato{1} into a medium dice.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together half the @Dijon mustard{2%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), half the @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir in as much minced shallot as you like.

> For 4 servings, use all the vinegar, 2 TBSP olive oil, and ½ tsp sugar.

Place half the garlic and @butter{1%tbsp} in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted and fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Brush garlic butter onto cut sides of baguette; season with salt and pepper. Place cut sides up on a #baking sheet{}.

Toast on top rack until lightly golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest. Tent with foil to keep warm.

Return same pan to medium heat. Add sliced shallot and cook until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add remaining garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @chicken demi-glace{1}, remaining mustard, @water{1/4%cup}, and a big pinch of pepper. Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%oz} and tomato with vinaigrette to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise. Halve garlic bread on a diagonal.

Divide chicken, arugula salad, and garlic bread between plates. Spoon pan sauce over chicken and serve.